@StoutStoutShako I'll just say it would be outside the scope of my current project and leave it at that.

@Mely_Shanight I think the best piece is advice I could give you is to just block or mute anyone who comes into your mentions looking to pick a fight about something as silly as fictional characters. Some people just want to argue and ruin your day, so don't let them.

@CerezaSakura Thank you. I really wish I could just write but trading in my desk job to write fics for people wouldn't let me pay rent.

I just feel sad about it. I feel guilty for taking time to relax because of I would just keep pushing, I could write more.  Even if I know I'd just burn out.

@doridoripawaa It wasn't like they were pushy. It's more like they were hopeful...

I guess one thing I wrote really impressed them and they'd like more but I'm not sure it's in me to write more of it right now. Up to my standards, anyway.

@raidpirate You know how this fandom can be... especially given the difference between what I'm writing now and what they're asking for.

I'll try to give it a lot of thought and give them a kind, if disappointing, answer.
Someone PM'd me in FFnet, but I don't really know what to say other than sorry. Is it ruder to say no and dash their hopes or to just ignore it and leave them without closure? I don't know.

I really don't know how to respond to this PM. I wish I had infinite time to write every story everyone ever wanted, but I only have a limited amount of time to write. My current project is something I'm pouring a lot of time and effort into. Sorry if it's not what you like.
